---
import Header from '../../components/Header.astro';
import BaseHead from '../../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';

const pageTitle = 'Best Portable Monitor for Work 2026';
const pageDescription = 'Honest review of portable USB-C monitors. Dual-screen productivity on the go without breaking the bank.';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription} />
    <style>
      main { max-width: 720px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: #333; }
      h1 { color: #232f3e; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
      .meta { color: #666; font-size: 0.9rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
      .product-box { background: #f8f9fa; border-radius: 8px; padding: 1.5rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
      .product-box h2 { margin-top: 0; }
      .product-box ul { padding-left: 1.2rem; }
      .btn { display: inline-block; background: #ff9900; color: #000; padding: 12px 24px; text-decoration: none; border-radius: 4px; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 0.5rem; }
      .btn:hover { background: #e68a00; }
      .disclaimer { font-size: 0.8rem; color: #888; margin-top: 3rem; border-top: 1px solid #eee; padding-top: 1rem; }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <h1>Best Portable Monitor for Work</h1>
      <div class="meta">Updated May 2026 · Under $150</div>

      <p>A second screen is the fastest way to boost productivity. But if you work from coffee shops, coworking spaces, or switch between home and office, a full-size monitor is impractical. A 15.6-inch portable monitor solves this without adding bulk.</p>

      <div class="product-box">
        <h2>🏆 Arzopa 15.6" Portable Monitor</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>1080p IPS panel</strong> — sharp text and accurate colors</li>
          <li><strong>Single USB-C cable</strong> — power + video, no adapter mess</li>
          <li><strong>Ultra-slim 0.3 inch</strong> — fits in laptop bag alongside your main machine</li>
          <li><strong>Built-in kickstand</strong> — adjustable angle, no extra case needed</li>
          <li><strong>Works with Mac, Windows, iPad, Switch</strong></li>
        </ul>
        <a href="https://www.amazon.com/s?k=portable+monitor+15.6&tag=toolwise20-20" class="btn" target="_blank" rel="noopener sponsored">Check Current Price on Amazon</a>
      </div>

      <h3>Why it beats a full-size monitor for mobile workers</h3>
      <p>You do not need 27 inches when you are writing code, editing documents, or managing spreadsheets on the road. A 15.6-inch screen at arm length is the same perceived size as a 24-inch desktop monitor. The USB-C single-cable setup means you unpack, plug in, and work in under 10 seconds.</p>

      <h3>Who should buy it</h3>
      <p>Digital nomads, hybrid workers, and anyone who brings a laptop to meetings but needs a second screen at their temporary desk. It is also a solid budget option for students who want dual monitors in a dorm without the desk space commitment.</p>

      <div class="disclaimer">
        Disclosure: As an Amazon Associate I earn from qualifying purchases. This review is based on independent research and reader feedback.
      </div>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>